run docker desktop

install application
    mvn clean install -DskipTests

change security of new shell script execute below command in terminal inside docker-compose directory
    chmod +x check-config-server-started.sh

then run all the containers using below command, execute below commands inside docker-compose directory
    docker compose -f common.yml -f kafka_cluster.yml down
    docker compose up
    docker ps

check logs using twitter-to-kafka service container id
    docker logs -f container-id

for check twitter messages comes into topics
    kafkacat -C -b localhost:19092 -t twitter-topic

connect to container shell
    docker exec -it container-id/bin/bash
then you can execute commands inside a container(twitter-to-kafka-service)
    ls
    cd ./cnb/lifecycle/
    ls
***from below command we can see container stats like memory
    top







